summary: Adds a new ( preety spacious ) worldspace to Your mod. No LOD or Navmesh included, 2 small areas undone for your personal taste purposes and a possibility of making the worldspace bigger.
descriptionHtml:
Requirements: Newest version of Skyrim, Dawnguard

This modder resource contains one preety spacious worldspace: Kersilivas. It has its own climate. All the objects added by it have name starting with "KER" - this involves object from other modder resources . This worldspace haven't got LOD or Navmesh generated. There are 2 interiors done - cathedra and a corridor which is neccesary to see the part of Ker'silivas. A placeholder entrance to it is located in riverwood ( amazingly big statue, impossible to miss) - it takes You to a small Island where You can take a boat to the much larger part of this world.

There are 2 parts of world that are undone to let You create whatever you want there. One is on the top of a mountain the second one envolves an unfinished road which opens a possibility of making the worldspace more complex.

All Creation Kit warnings does not affect working of this modder resource.

If You noticed any buggs ( object misplaced) feel free to inform me in the comments and I am going to fix them as soon as possible.

Thanks to:

Project Hoddminir team for publishing their useful resources ( Elinen, Ztree)
Stroti for his cathedra
Blary for his wall art and opened books resources.

Feel free to make a use out of it ( consider crediting me but it's not necesarry) I am also looking for a bit of feedback
author: Nevervell
